Chief Whip of the 9th House of Representatives, Tahir Monguno (APC, Borno), has charged parliamentary reporters to project the National Assembly in good light. This, he added, was to help correct the lack of confidence and negative impression already formed about the institution and the lawmakers in the minds of average Nigerians. Monguno, who stated this yesterday when a delegation of the National Assembly reporters paid him a courtesy visit, noted that “parliamentary reporters have a role to mould and reshape the public perception about the workings of the National Assembly.” OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE “As representatives of the people, our responsibility is huge; aside law making, we also assist in solving problems. “Unless journalists covering the parliament make it mandatory to propagate their legislative business, the public might not come to terms with our primary constitutional responsibilities,” the Borno lawmaker submitted. Earlier in her remarks, Chairman of the House of Representatives press corps, Grace Ike of Silver Bird Television, expressed satisfaction with the Chief Whip, and pledged a cordial working relationship with the 9th House of Representatives. Of budget cut, National Assembly and institutional blackmail APC lawmakers in final push for principal officers Battle for NASS Principal Officers, ‘Juicy Committees’ Hots Up Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin